File: SAA's business rescue practitioners have to present a final rescue plan by 15 June. JOHANNESBURG - Unions at SAA have slammed the latest business rescue plan for the ailing carrier. Numsa and Sacca are accusing the Public Enterprises department of being dishonest in its dealings. READ: SAA may take off again The unions say their operating model presented to the department has been disregarded. Business rescue practitioners are proposing SAA's staff be cut to 1,000 employees.